Mutabor core functionality

This group contains the functions that deal with the core idea of Mutabor: Parse Mutabor source files and use the generated memory structures to manage tunings, logics and retunings. Mehr ...

Zusammengehörigkeiten von Mutabor core functionality:

Freundbeziehungen

class mutabor::cow_container< C >::iterator::const_iterator
 

Ausführliche Beschreibung

This group contains the functions that deal with the core idea of Mutabor: Parse Mutabor source files and use the generated memory structures to manage tunings, logics and retunings.

The microtonal part can be given in the double value.

intervala double value that represents the interval. a semitone is represented as 1.00, and an octave as 12.00

interval in the internal representation of Mutabor.


Zu beachten
The resulting interval is always a valid non-nil interval.

Add the distance of t1 - t2 to offset. 


This function transfers the interval between two tones to two other tones.


Parameter

  

    
offsetnew base tone 

    
t1old tone 

    
t2old base tone

  

  




Rückgabe
offset + (t1 - t2)

  104 {
  105         // fill using a pattern of coprime numbers. So that we can check correct assumption about filling.
  106         // group theory tells us that each modulus by division by MUT_BOX_MAX_KEY_INDEX+1 is contained an equal number of times.
  107 
  108         for (size_t i = 0 ; i < 7 * (MUT_BOX_MAX_KEY_INDEX+1) * 5; i++) {
  109                 int box = i % 7;
  110                 int noteidx = (i*5);
  111                 size_t last = boxes[box].last_key;
  112                 CPPUNIT_ASSERT( i >= 7 || last == 0);
  113                 CPPUNIT_ASSERT(boxes[box].key_count == (i/7));
  114                 mutabor_note_type * note = mutabor_create_key_in_box(&boxes[box]);
  115                 CPPUNIT_ASSERT(note!=NULL);
  116                 note->number = noteidx;
  117                 note->id = i/7;
  118                 CPPUNIT_ASSERT(boxes[box].key_count == (i/7) + 1);

  121                 CPPUNIT_ASSERT(boxes[box].last_key == (i/7));
